Reviewed `src/blog/people/drafts/Margaret-Qualley.md` and appended a `FRESH EYES REVIEW` block at the bottom. No body edits.

**The two biggest issues:**

1. **Maid is completely absent** — zero mentions in a 2,200-word profile. It's her Golden Globe-nominated lead, Netflix's most-watched limited series at launch, and the one project she *engineered*: she pitched Margot Robbie on casting Andie MacDowell as her character's mentally ill mother. The draft's thesis is "she hands the scorecard to whichever director will hold it" — Maid is the one time she built the measuring device herself and aimed it at the person who generates the nepo-baby charge she keeps volunteering. Related: MacDowell exists in this draft only as a testimony quote and a woman leaving a premiere, and her own on-camera deflection about working with her mother ("a very very sweet experience... I don't know if that answers your question") is sitting unused in the local transcripts.

2. **The Kenzo World ad is missing from a piece titled "Why She Breaks at Dance."** Spike Jonze, 2016, largely improvised. Her breakout cultural moment was dancing with no correct execution — exactly what she says she left ballet to find. The draft has three dance nodes available and uses two, and the missing one is the one that keeps the argument from being too tidy.

Also flagged: the skeptic section concedes only that her *movies* are bad while she's great (a compliment in a skeptic's coat), there's not one sentence describing what she actually does on screen, the ballet arithmetic is restated five times, and the Shia LaBeouf omission should be a deliberate call rather than a default given the closing section narrates the Antonoff separation in detail.

Sources for the reality check: [Netflix Tudum on the Maid casting pitch](https://www.netflix.com/tudum/articles/margaret-qualley-asked-margot-robbie-to-cast-her-mom-in-maid), [Golden Globes nominee profile](https://goldenglobes.com/articles/nominee-profile-2022-margaret-qualley-maid/), [Kenzo World ad](https://tv.booooooom.com/2016/08/30/ad-day-kenzo-world-spike-jonze/), [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Margaret_Qualley).
